7.62x54r Silver Tip Ammo - 440rd Spam Can
Manufacturer: Bulgaria/Russia
manufactured in the early 70's through the 80's

The Silver Tipped 149 grain Boat Tail bullet in this ammunition is unique in that it has a steel shank in the center of the projectile beneath an exterior coating of lead that is bonded to the bullet jacket. This allows the projectile to stabilize in flight and provides the accuracy and penetration of a steel core round while not being harsh on the barrel or bore as is the case with a full hardened steel core. It is the absolute best of both worlds.
Also, the Boat Tail Bullet is more aerodynamic and allows for a flatter trajectory and greater accuracy over a long distance.
This ammo has a copper washed steel case and is berdan primed. The case neck and the primer are sealed for moisture protection. It comes packed in 20rd. military packs, 440rds. per sealed spam can.

title: For Sale:  Portable Biometric Gun Safe
postcontent:
I bought a few of these to get a deal on one-I am loosing money on these but I need to unload-great way to keep your guns away from the kids while on the car or keep jewelry or documents safe while you are on the road.
This new Biometric portable safe box provides you with sleek, safe & convenient storage for handguns, jewelry, coins, stamps and personal documents or anything you want to keep safe. Your valuables can be quickly accessed via the biometric finger scanner-takes less than 1 second to open. Its compact size also allows you to store your valuables in tight spaces or even while traveling. The battery life is over 1000+ swipes on four AA batteries (not included) 
Dimensions:
•	 - Outer Dimension: 7-1/2"x12-3/4"x2"
•	 - Inner Dimension: 7-1/4"x10-1/4"x1-3/4"

Biometric Resolution: 500DPI
Verification and comparison time: ≤1s
False rejection rate (FRR): ≤0.01%;
False acceptance rate (FAR): ≤0.0001%;
Battery Life: Approx 16 months

Door opening mode: The electric lock will unlock for 3 seconds after the user passes finger print over sensor, if the cover is not opened 3 seconds after the fingerprint pass the unit will re-lock itself

FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS

What happens to the fingerprints that are stored in the Biometric portable safe box when the batteries die?
The Biometric portable safe box retains all fingerprints in the event of total power loss. Once the power is restored by inserting new batteries the unit will function as it did before the power loss.

Is the Biometric portable safe box fire proof?
No, the Biometric portable safe box is not fire proof or fire resistant. The Biometric portable safe box has been specifically designed for secure access control and convenience.


If I cut my finger, does the fingerprint heal the same as before and will it open my safe?
Usually yes, although if the cut is significant or requires stitches, scar tissue may form as a result causing a change in your fingerprint. That is why we recommend enrolling additional user fingerprints and also fingerprints from your other hand.


Will the Biometric portable safe box scan my finger correctly when my finger/fingerprint is puffy after a shower/swimming?
The Biometric portable safe box has been designed to be very sensitive when authenticating and matching fingerprints. The unit will open when your fingerprint has increased moisture from after an average shower or swim and will open. There may be times when extreme water retention due to extended time in the water will cause a minuet aspect of your fingerprints to change for a short time and access to your Biometric portable safe box may be denied until your fingerprint returns to its ordinary normal condition the same as when you originally enrolled that print.


Can someone cutoff my finger and try to use it to open the Biometric portable safe box?
No, Biometric portable safe box uses technology that detects live fingers for scanning, so in the unfortunate event that a detached finger is used to attempt access the unit will not open. 

Included:
Fingerprint safe box
Keys x 2(for use if battery dies)
Security Cable(for attaching safe to car seat or any fixed object) 
Manual – English
Elastic security strap

Offered in .45 ACP only, the R100 has a matte-black finish and comes standard with Hogue® rubber grips. The slide is manufactured from CNC machined bar stock with a low-cut ejection port, the frame is steel investment cast, and the barrel is hammer forged stainless steel—all manufactured to ISO 9001 and NATO AQAP 120 quality standards.

The Regent R100 accepts virtually all aftermarket parts made for M1911-style pistols, giving you the ability to customize your pistol. Also, almost all aftermarket accessories
designed for M1911-styles can be added, whether it be specialized custom grips, added sights, tactical enhancements, or other customizations.

For Manufacturer's website and videos visit: http://regentarms.com/products/models/r100.html

title: For Sale:  NIB Bushmaster XM-15 AR-15 (not Carbon) with ammo & lots of extras
postcontent:
I have a brand new all-metal Bushmaster XM 15 Optics Ready Carbine with 16" chrome-lined A4-style barrel for sale. Not "brand new with only 100 rounds through it" but totally new. I've never even loaded it! This is a quality Bushmaster, and not a cheaper DPMS product, or a plastic Carbon 15.

Comes with:
-Factory box
-2 metal 30-round Bushmaster magazines
-Empty chamber indicator flag
-Lock and key
-Sling
-2 rail risers in case you want to use a big scope
-Warranty
-Owner's manual
-and whatever extra paperwork/coupons/etc might be included normally. 

It is factory built with the receiver-length picatinny rail, 6-position adjustable stock, A2 flash suppressor, bayonet lug, and sling swivels. And unlike most modern AR's, it is stamped on the mag well so you know it accepts BOTH .223 AND 5.56 ammunition, whatever you can find to use - no guessing that the NATO rounds MIGHT go boom without your gun going BOOM!

Also included is:
-A brand new (in the unopened box) BSA 42 mm red-dot scope sight with built-on sun shade
-100 rounds of new brass PMC X-Tac 5.56 55 gr FMJ (perfect military round for this barrel)
-A brand new Tapco Intrafuse AR spanner wrench with a mil-spec castle wrench, receiver extension removal wrench, and A1/A2 flash suppressor wrench. It is manganese phosphate coated for durability, and has a lifetime warranty
-A brand new weather-resistant ammo box large enough for all the extras to fit in

No need to worry about someone's garage build, or whether “100 rounds down range” really means 100 rounds or 5,000.  Plus you can get it sighted in on the range and have some fun banging away without having to wait a couple months to find some clean ammo, or pay $1 a round.

The base model MSRP on this is $1,391.48, and with this deal you avoid taxes, fees, and snoopy government agents.  I saw these at the last gun show going for around $1600 without any extras, so I'm listing it at $1550 (with ammo, red dot, wrench, and ammo box).  Face-to-face cash sale, prefer you have a CCW but not required.

I also have a brand new rail-mountable tactical laser/light combo with pressure switches I can throw in for an extra $40.  I do have up to a couple hundred extra rounds of the X-Tac 5.56 rounds in boxes of 20 I'm willing to sell for the right price with this rifle.

If you have any questions, please feel free to ask.  However, do not ask if this is still available.  If the ad is up, the gun is still for sale.  Do not e-mail me telling me you saw this at Cabella's for $850 two days ago – you're lying and we both know it.  I'll just laugh at you, and probably put your idiocy and name on display in my next gun article for the world to laugh at you.  Ditto if you e-mail me with any other complaints or gripes without actually displaying any interest in the rifle.

Prefer the cash, but may be willing to accept a partial trade for a Bersa Thunder in 9mm or .45 cal.
